            <div id="working-prompts" class="prompts-container">
                <div class="prompt-category">
                    <h3>üìã Scenario A: Werkstudent Role ‚Äì No Experience</h3>
                    <div class="prompt-item">
                        <h4>üéØ Complete Job Search & CV Creation Prompt</h4>
                        <div class="prompt-content">
                            <strong>Background Information to Provide:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Degree and field of study</li>
                                <li>University and current semester</li>
                                <li>Relevant coursework or academic projects</li>
                                <li>Tools, software, or methods you're familiar with</li>
                                <li>German and English language level</li>
                                <li>Weekly availability (hours)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>Copy-Paste Prompt:</strong>
                            <p>"I am a [degree] student at [university], currently in [semester]. I have completed coursework in [list courses] and worked on [mention 1-2 academic projects]. I am familiar with [tools/software]. My German level is [A1-C2] and English is [level]. I can work [X] hours per week. I have no prior work experience. Please:

1. Suggest 5-7 realistic Werkstudent roles suitable for someone with no work experience
2. Explain which roles are typically open to international students in Germany
3. Rewrite my academic profile into a professional one-page CV that highlights my strengths and transferable skills
4. Prepare strong, confident answers to the question: 'Do you have practical experience?'
5. Advise how to position myself as reliable, structured, and eager to learn"</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="prompt-category">
                    <h3>üìä Scenario B: Werkstudent Role ‚Äì Early Experience (0-2 Years)</h3>
                    <div class="prompt-item">
                        <h4>üéØ Experience Optimization Prompt</h4>
                        <div class="prompt-content">
                            <strong>Background Information to Provide:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Degree and field of study</li>
                                <li>Previous internships, working student jobs, or part-time roles</li>
                                <li>Key responsibilities you handled</li>
                                <li>Tools, systems, or processes you used</li>
                                <li>Target Werkstudent role or industry</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>Copy-Paste Prompt:</strong>
                            <p>"I am a [degree] student with [0-2 years] of experience in [industry/role]. Previously, I worked as [role] where I [key responsibilities]. I used [tools/systems]. I am now applying for Werkstudent positions in [target industry]. Please:

1. Align my existing experience with German market expectations for Werkstudent roles
2. Rewrite my CV bullet points using impact-oriented and contribution-focused language
3. Identify any gaps in my profile and suggest how to close them quickly (within 4-6 weeks)
4. Draft a short, professional email to HR expressing interest in a Werkstudent position
5. Highlight what German recruiters will value most in my profile"</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="prompt-category">
                    <h3>üîÑ Scenario C: Career Shift / Role Change ‚Äì No German Experience</h3>
                    <div class="prompt-item">
                        <h4>üéØ Career Transition Prompt</h4>
                        <div class="prompt-content">
                            <strong>Background Information to Provide:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Previous role or industry</li>
                                <li>Target role or field in Germany</li>
                                <li>Transferable skills from previous experience</li>
                                <li>Reason for career change</li>
                                <li>Current education or upskilling efforts</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>Copy-Paste Prompt:</strong>
                            <p>"I previously worked in [previous role/industry] and am now transitioning to [target field] in Germany. My transferable skills include [list skills]. I am making this change because [reason]. I am currently [studying/upskilling] in [area]. Please:

1. Identify and highlight my transferable skills that are relevant to the new role
2. Rewrite my CV to reduce perceived hiring risk for German employers
3. Help me position this career shift as logical and intentional, not desperate
4. Prepare convincing interview answers that explain my transition confidently
5. Highlight what German recruiters will worry about regarding my profile and how to proactively address these concerns"</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

