                <div class="prompt-category">
                    <h3>üìö 1. Mandatory Internship (Pflichtpraktikum) ‚Äì No Experience</h3>
                    <div class="prompt-item">
                        <h4>üéØ Complete Application Package Prompt</h4>
                        <div class="prompt-content">
                            <strong>Background Information to Provide:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Degree and specialization</li>
                                <li>University and current semester</li>
                                <li>Relevant coursework and academic projects</li>
                                <li>Tools, software, or methods you know</li>
                                <li>German language level (A1‚ÄìC1)</li>
                                <li>Confirmation that internship is mandatory</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>Copy-Paste Prompt:</strong>
                            <p>"I am a [degree] student at [university], semester [X]. I need to complete a mandatory internship (Pflichtpraktikum). My relevant coursework includes [courses], and I have experience with [tools/software]. My German level is [A1-C2]. Please:

1. Suggest 5-7 suitable Pflichtpraktikum roles aligned with my academic profile
2. Translate my coursework and academic projects into CV-ready professional experience
3. Create a one-page, ATS-friendly CV following German standards
4. List 10 common German interview questions for Pflichtpraktikum candidates with strong example answers
5. Highlight frequent mistakes international students make in applications and how to avoid them"</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="prompt-category">
                    <h3>üí° 2. Voluntary Internship (Freiwilliges Praktikum) ‚Äì No Experience</h3>
                    <div class="prompt-item">
                        <h4>üéØ First-Timer Application Prompt</h4>
                        <div class="prompt-content">
                            <strong>Background Information to Provide:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Degree or field of study</li>
                                <li>University and study focus</li>
                                <li>Transferable skills or academic strengths</li>
                                <li>Availability and preferred duration</li>
                                <li>Language skills</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>Copy-Paste Prompt:</strong>
                            <p>"I am studying [degree] at [university] with focus on [area]. I have no prior work experience but possess strong [transferable skills]. I am available for [duration] and speak [languages]. Please:

1. Explain what German recruiters realistically expect from voluntary interns with no experience
2. Rewrite my profile to emphasize learning ability, reliability, structure, and potential
3. Draft a short German-style cover letter (Anschreiben) that addresses my lack of experience positively
4. Suggest strong, honest answers to common 'no experience' interview questions
5. Advise which voluntary internship types are most accessible for complete beginners"</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
