            <div id="fulltime-prompts" class="prompts-container">
                <div class="prompt-category">
                    <h3>üíº 1. Full-Time Job Applications ‚Äì With Experience</h3>
                    <div class="prompt-item">
                        <h4>üéØ Professional CV & Cover Letter Prompt</h4>
                        <div class="prompt-content">
                            <strong>Background Information to Provide:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Degree and specialization</li>
                                <li>Graduation month and year</li>
                                <li>Relevant internships or work experience</li>
                                <li>Target job roles and industries</li>
                                <li>Key tools, systems, or methodologies</li>
                                <li>Language proficiency (German/English)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>Copy-Paste Prompt:</strong>
                            <p>"I graduated with a [degree] in [month/year] with specialization in [area]. I have [X years/months] of experience through [internships/jobs]. I am targeting [roles] in [industry]. I have used [tools/systems]. My German is [level] and English is [level]. Please:

1. Rewrite my entire CV to position me as fully job-ready for competitive full-time roles in Germany
2. Optimize my CV specifically for German ATS (Applicant Tracking Systems) and recruiter screening patterns
3. Tailor the language, tone, and structure to match German market expectations (directness, clarity, results-focus)
4. Draft a professional, compelling German-style cover letter (Anschreiben) for my target role
5. Proactively highlight my strengths while addressing potential concerns (e.g., visa status, language, experience gaps)"</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="prompt-category">
                    <h3>üé§ 2. Full-Time Interview Preparation (Germany-Focused)</h3>
                    <div class="prompt-item">
                        <h4>üéØ Mock Interview & Evaluation Prompt</h4>
                        <div class="prompt-content">
                            <strong>Background Information to Provide:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Target role and company type</li>
                                <li>Years of experience</li>
                                <li>Job description (if available)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>Copy-Paste Prompt:</strong>
                            <p>"I am interviewing for a [role] position at a [startup/corporate/SME] in Germany. I have [X years] of experience. Here is the job description: [paste JD]. Please:

1. Conduct a realistic mock interview for this full-time role with 10 common German interview questions
2. After each of my answers, provide detailed evaluation on structure, clarity, cultural fit, and impact
3. Explain specifically what German interviewers value in strong answers (directness, evidence, humility, professionalism)
4. Suggest improved versions of weak answers with examples
5. Highlight common interview mistakes that graduates make when applying in Germany and how to avoid them"</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

